obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (2104)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2104&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Coal Bearing Areas`
  line `(Acquisition and Development) Act, 1957.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India, except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^1as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 12th June, 1957, vide Notification No. S.R.O. 1931 (E), dated 10th June, 1957, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(i).`
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (2105)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1957, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-6-1957).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2105&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "competent authority" means any person appointed to be a competent authority under`
  line `section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Government company" means a Government company as defined in section 617 of the`
  line `Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), in which any land or rights in or over land shall have vested under`
  line `section 11;`
  line
  line `(c) "Mineral Concession Rules" means the rules for the time being in force made under the Mines`
  line `and Minerals (Regulation and Development) Act, 1948 (53 of 1948);`
  line
  line `^1[(cc) "mining lease" includes a mining sub-lease, and "lessee" shall be construed accordingly;]`
  line
  line `(d) the expression "person interested" includes all persons claiming an interest in compensation to`
  line `be made on account of the acquisition of land, or of the acquisition, extinguishment or modification`
  line `of any rights in or over land, under this Act;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "Tribunal" means the Tribunal constituted under section 14.`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (2106)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Appointment of competent authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2106&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint any person to be the competent authority for the purposes of this Act; and`
  line `different persons may be appointed as competent authorities for different provisions of this Act and for`
  line `different areas.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (2107)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Preliminary notification respecting intention to prospect for coal in any area and powers of competent authorities thereupon.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2107&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever it appears to the Central Government that coal is`
  line `likely to be obtained from land in any locality, it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, give notice`
  line `of its intention to prospect for coal therein.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under sub-section (1) shall give a brief description of the land and state its`
  line `approximate area.`
  line
  line `(3) On the issue of a notification under sub-section (1), it shall be lawful for the competent authority`
  line `and for his servants and workmen--`
  line
  line `(a) to enter upon and survey any land in such locality;`
  line
  line `(b) to dig or bore into the sub-soil;`
  line
  line `(c) to do all other acts necessary to prospect for coal in the land;`
  line
  line `(d) to set out the boundaries of the land in which prospecting is proposed to be done and the`
  line `intended line of the work, if any, proposed to be made thereon;`
  line
  line `(e) to mark such boundaries and line by placing marks; and`
  line
  line `(f) where otherwise the survey cannot be completed and the boundaries and line marked, to cut`
  line `down and clear away any part of any standing crop, fence or jungle:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall enter into any building or upon any enclosed court or garden attached to`
  line `a dwelling house (unless with the consent of the occupier thereof) without previously giving such`
  line `occupier at least seven days' notice in writing of his intention to do so.`
  line
  line `(4) In issuing a notification under this section the Central Government shall exclude therefrom that`
  line `portion of any land in which coal mining operations are actually being carried on in conformity with the`
  line `provisions of any enactment, rule or order for the time being in force or any premises on which any`
  line `process ancillary to the getting, dressing or preparation for sale of coal obtained as a result of such`
  line `operations is being carried on are situate.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (2108)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Effect of notification on prospecting licences and mining leases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2108&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `On the issue of a notification`
  line `under sub-section (1) of section 4 in respect of any land--`
  line
  line `(a) any prospecting licence ^1[which authorises any person] to prospect for coal or any other`
  line `mineral in the land shall cease to have effect; and`
  line
  line `(b) any mining lease ^2*** shall, in so far as it authorises the lessee or any person claiming`
  line `through him to undertake any operation in the land, cease to have effect for so long as the notification`
  line `under that sub-section is in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 1957, s. 3, for "granted to any person under the Mineral Concession Rules which authorises`
  line `him" (w.e.f. 12-6-1957).`
  line
  line `2 The words "granted to any person under the Mineral Concession Rules" omitted by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-6-1957).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (2109)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Compensation for any necessary damage done under section 4.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2109&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whenever any action of`
  line `the nature described in sub-section (3) of section 4 is to be taken, the competent authority shall, before or`
  line `at the time such action is taken, pay or tender payment for all necessary damage which is likely to be`
  line `caused, and in case of dispute as to the sufficiency of the amount so paid or tendered or as to the person to`
  line `whom it should be paid or tendered, he shall at once refer the dispute to the decision of the Central`
  line `Government, and the decision of the Central Government shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) The fact that there exists any such dispute as is referred to in this section shall not be a bar to`
  line `action under sub-section (3) of section 4.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (2110)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Power to acquire land or rights in or over land notified under section 4.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2110&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central`
  line `Government is satisfied that coal is obtainable in the whole or any part of the land notified under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4, it may, within a period of two years from the date of the said notification or`
  line `within such further period not exceeding one year in the aggregate as the Central Government may`
  line `specify in this behalf, by notification in the Official Gazette, give notice of its intention to acquire the`
  line `whole or any part of the land or of any rights in or over such land, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `(2) If no notice to acquire the land or any rights in or over such land is given under sub-section (1)`
  line `within the period allowed thereunder, the notification issued under sub-section (1) of section 4 shall cease`
  line `to have effect on the expiration of three years from the date thereof.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (2111)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Objections to acquisition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1971, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 11-12-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2111&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person interested in any land in respect of which a`
  line `notification under section 7 has been issued may, within thirty days of the issue of the notification, object`
  line `to the acquisition of the whole or any part of the land or of any rights in or over such land.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--It shall not be an objection within the meaning of this section for any person to say`
  line `that he himself desires to undertake mining operations in the land for the production of coal and that such`
  line `operations should not be undertaken by the Central Government or by any other person.`
  line
  line `(2) Every objection under sub-section (1) shall be made to the competent authority in writing, and the`
  line `competent authority shall give the objector an opportunity of being heard either in person or by a legal`
  line `practitioner and shall, after hearing all such objections and after making such further inquiry, if any,`
  line `as he thinks necessary,`
  line `^1[either make a report in respect of the land which has been notified under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 7 or of rights in or over such land, or make different reports in respect of`
  line `different parcels of such land or of rights in or over such land, to the Central Government, containing his`
  line `recommendations on the objections, together with the record of the proceedings held by him, for the`
  line `decision of that Government.]`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, a person shall be deemed to be interested in land who would be`
  line `entitled to claim an interest in compensation if the land or any rights in or over such land were acquired`
  line `under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (2112)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Declaration of acquisition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2112&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) When the Central Government is satisfied, after considering the`
  line `report, if any, made under section 8 that any land or any rights in or over such land should be acquired, a`
  line `declaration shall be made by it to that effect ^1[, and different declarations may be made from time to time`
  line `in respect of different parcels of any land, or of rights in or over such land, covered by the same`
  line `notification under sub-section (1) of section 7, irrespective of whether one report or different reports has`
  line `or have been made (wherever required) under sub-section (2) of section 8]:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that no declaration in respect of any particular land, or rights in or over such land, covered`
  line `by a notification under sub-section (1) of section 7, issued after the commencement of the Coal Bearing`
  line `Areas (Acquisition and Development) Amendment and Validation Act, 1971 (54 of 1971), shall be made`
  line `after the expiry of three years from the date of the said notification:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, where a declaration] relates to any land or to any rights in or over land`
  line `belonging to a State Government which has or have not been leased out, no such declaration shall be`
  line `made except after previous consultation with the State Government.`
  line
  line `(2)`
  line `^3[Every declaration] shall be published in the Official Gazette, and--`
  line
  line `(a) in any case where land is to be acquired, shall state the district or other territorial division in`
  line `which the land is situate and its approximate area; and, where a plan shall have been made of the`
  line `land, the place where such plan may be inspected;`
  line
  line `(b) in any case where rights in or over such land are to be acquired, shall state the nature and`
  line `extent of the rights in addition to the matters relating to the land specified in clause (a); and`
  line
  line `a copy of every such declaration shall be sent to the State Government concerned.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f 11-12-1971).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Provided that, where the declaration" (w.e.f. 11-12-1971).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "The declaration" (w.e.f. 11-12-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (2113)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 10
  title `Special powers in cases of urgency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 51 of 1957, s. 4 (w.e.f 12-6-1957).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2113&sectionno=9A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[9A. Special powers in cases of urgency.--If the Central Government is satisfied that it is`
  line `necessary to acquire immediately the whole or any part of the land notified under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 4 or any rights in or over such land, the Central Government may direct that the provisions of`
  line `section 8 shall not apply, and if it does so direct, a declaration may be made under section 9 in respect`
  line `thereof at any time after the issue of the notification under section 7.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (2114)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title `Vesting of land or rights in Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2114&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) On the publication in the Official`
  line `Gazette of the declaration under section 9, the land or the rights in or over the land, as the case may be,`
  line `shall vest absolutely in the Central Government ^1[free from all encumbrances].`
  line
  line `(2) Where the rights under any mining lease ^2[granted or deemed to have been granted by a State`
  line `Government] to any person are acquired under this Act, the Central Government shall, on and from the`
  line `date of such vesting, be deemed to have become the lessee of the State Government as if a mining lease`
  line `under the Mineral Concession Rules had been granted by the State Government to the Central`
  line `Government, the period thereof being the entire period for which such a lease could have been granted by`
  line `the State Government under those rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 12-6-1957)`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 51 of 1957, s. 5, for "granted by a State Government" (w.e.f. 12-6-1957).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (2115)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of Central Government to direct vesting of land or rights in a Government company.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2115&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 10, the Central Government may, if it is`
  line `satisfied that a Government company is willing to comply, or has complied, with such terms and`
  line `conditions as the Central Government may think fit to impose, direct, by order in writing, that the land or`
  line `the rights in or over the land, as the case may be, shall, instead of vesting in the Central Government`
  line `under section 10 or continuing to so vest, vest in the Government company either on the date of`
  line `publication of the declaration or on such other date as may be specified in the direction.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the rights under any mining lease acquired under this Act vest in a Government company`
  line `under sub-section (1), the Government company shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to`
  line `have become the lessee of the State Government as if a mining lease under the Mineral Concession Rules`
  line `had been granted by the State Government to the Government company, the period thereof being the`
  line `entire period for which such a lease could have been granted by the State Government under those rules;`
  line `and all the rights and liabilities of the Central Government in relation to the lease or the land covered by it`
  line `shall, on and from the date of such vesting, be deemed to have become the rights and liabilities of the`
  line `Government company.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (2116)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to take possession of land acquired.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2116&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority may, by notice in`
  line `writing, require any person in possession of any land acquired under this Act to surrender or deliver`
  line `possession of the land within such period as may be specified in the notice, and if a person refuses or fails`
  line `to comply with any such notice, the competent authority may enter upon and take possession of the land,`
  line `and for that purpose may use or cause to be used such force as may be necessary.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (2117)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Compensation for prospecting licences ceasing to have effect, rights under mining leases being acquired, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2117&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where a prospecting licence ceases to have effect under section 5, there shall`
  line `be paid to the person interested compensation, the amount of which shall be a sum made up of all items of`
  line `reasonable and bona fide expenditure actually incurred in respect of the land, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `(i) the expenditure incurred in obtaining the licence;`
  line
  line `(ii) the expenditure, if any, incurred in respect of the preparation of maps, charts and other`
  line `documents relating to the land, the collection from the land of cores or other mineral samples and the`
  line `due analysis thereof and the preparation of any other relevant records or material;`
  line
  line `(iii) the expenditure, if any, incurred in respect of the construction of roads or other essential`
  line `works on the land, if such roads or works are in existence and in a usable condition;`
  line
  line `(iv) the expenditure, if any, incurred in respect of any other operation necessary for prospecting`
  line `carried out in the land.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the rights under a mining lease are acquired under this Act, there shall be paid to the`
  line `person interested compensation, the amount of which shall be a sum made up of the following items,`
  line namely,--
  line
  line `(i) if the lease was granted after prospecting operations had been carried out in respect of the land`
  line `under a prospecting licence, the sum of all items of reasonable and bona fide expenditure actually`
  line `incurred with respect to the matters specified in clauses (i), (ii), (iii) and (iv) of sub-section (1) before`
  line `the date of the lease:`
  line
  line `Provided that where two or more leases had been granted in relation to any land covered`
  line `previously by one prospecting licence, only so much of the expenditure aforesaid as bears to the total`
  line `expenditure the same proportion as the area under the mining lease in respect of which the rights have`
  line `been acquired bears to the total area covered by the mining leases shall be payable under this clause;`
  line
  line `(ii) any reasonable and bona fide expenditure of the nature referred to in clauses (i), (ii) and (iii)`
  line `of sub-section (1) actually incurred in relation to the lease, together with the salami, if any, paid for`
  line `obtaining the lease;`
  line
  line `(iii) the expenditure, if any, incurred by way of payment of dead-rent or minimum royalty during`
  line `any year or years when there was no production of coal;`
  line
  line `(iv) interest on any such expenditure referred to in clauses (i), (ii) and (iii) as has actually been`
  line `incurred ^1[up to] the year in which the rights under the lease are acquired, interest being calculated in`
  line `the following manner, that is to say,--`
  line
  line `interest at the rate of five per centum per annum in respect of the expenditure incurred during`
  line `each calendar year for the first five years commencing from the year in which such expenditure`
  line `was incurred plus interest at the rate of four per centum per annum in respect of each subsequent`
  line `year after the expiration of the first five years and ending with the year in which the rights under`
  line `the lease are acquired:`
  line
  line `Provided that the total sum payable under this clause shall not exceed one-half of the total amount`
  line `referred to in ^2[clauses (i), (ii) and (iii)].`
  line
  line `(3) Where the rights under a mining lease acquired under section 9 relate only to a part of the land`
  line `covered by the mining lease, the amount of compensation payable shall be such as bears to the total`
  line `compensation which would have been payable if the rights of the mining lessee in respect of the entire`
  line `land had been acquired, the same proportion which the area of the land in respect of which the rights are`
  line `acquired bears to the total area of the land covered by the mining lease.`
  line
  line `(4) Where a mining lease ceases to have effect for any period under clause (b) of section 5, there shall`
  line `be paid by way of compensation for the period during which the lease so ceased to have effect, a sum`
  line `equivalent to five per centum of any such expenditure as is referred to in clauses (i) and (iii) of`
  line `sub-section (2) for each year during which the lease remains suspended.`
  line
  line `(5) Where any land is acquired under section 9, there shall be paid compensation to the person`
  line `interested the amount of which shall be determined after taking into consideration--`
  line
  line `(a) the market value of the land at the date of the publication of the notification under`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--The value of any minerals lying in the land shall not be taken into consideration in`
  line `determining the market value of any land;`
  line
  line `(b) the damage sustained by the person interested, by reason of the taking of any standing crops`
  line `or trees which may be on the land at the time of the taking possession thereof;`
  line
  line `(c) the damage, if any, sustained by the person interested, at the time of taking possession of the`
  line `land, by reason of severing such land from other land;`
  line
  line `(d) the damage, if any, sustained by the person interested, at the time of taking possession of the`
  line `land, by reason of the acquisition injuriously affecting his other immovable property in any other`
  line `manner, or his earnings;`
  line
  line `(e) if, in consequence of the acquisition of the land, the person interested is compelled to change`
  line `his residence or place of business, the reasonable expenses, if any, incidental to such change; and`
  line
  line `(f) the damage, if any, bona fide resulting from diminution of the profits of the land between the`
  line `time of the publication of the notification under sub-section (1) of section 4 and the time of the`
  line `publication of the declaration under sub-section (2) of section 9.`
  line
  line `^3[(5A) In determining the amount of compensation for any land acquired under section 9, any increase`
  line `to the value of the other land of the person interested, likely to accrue from the use to which the land`
  line `acquired will be put shall not be taken into consideration.]`
  line
  line `(6) Where any operation carried on by or on behalf of the Central Government in the exercise of any`
  line `powers conferred by this Act causes or is likely to cause damage to the surface of any land or any works`
  line `thereon and in respect thereof no provision for compensation is made elsewhere in this Act, the competent`
  line `authority shall pay or tender payment for all such damage, and, in case of dispute as to the sufficiency of`
  line `the amount so paid or tendered or as to the person to whom it is to be paid or tendered, he shall refer the`
  line `dispute to the decision of the Tribunal.`
  line
  line `(7) No compensation under this section in relation to maps, charts and other documents shall be paid`
  line `unless the person to whom it is payable has delivered to the prescribed authority all the maps, charts and`
  line `other documents.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 1957, s. 6, for "during the period commencing from the date of the lease and ending with" (w.e.f. 12-6-1957).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "clauses (ii) and (iii)" (w.e.f. 12-6-1957).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 54 of 1971, s. 4 (w.e.f. 11-12-1971).`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (2118)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Method of determining compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 11-12-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2118&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the amount of any compensation payable`
  line `under this Act can be fixed by agreement, it shall be paid in accordance with such agreement.`
  line
  line `(2) Where no such agreement can be reached, the Central Government shall constitute a Tribunal`
  line `consisting of a person who is or has been or is qualified to be a Judge of a High Court for the purpose of`
  line `determining the amount.`
  line
  line `(3) The Central Government may in any particular case nominate a person having expert knowledge`
  line `in mining to assist the Tribunal, and where such nomination is made, the person or persons interested may`
  line `also nominate any other person for the same purpose.`
  line
  line `(4) At the commencement of the proceedings before the Tribunal the Central Government and the`
  line `person interested shall state what in their respective opinions is a fair amount of compensation.`
  line
  line `(5) The Tribunal shall after hearing the dispute, make an award determining the amount of`
  line `compensation which appears to it to be just, and specify the person or persons to whom the compensation`
  line `shall be paid; and in making the award the Tribunal shall have regard to the circumstances of each case`
  line `and to the foregoing provisions of this Act with respect to the manner in which the amount of`
  line `compensation shall be determined in so far as the said provisions or any of them may be applicable.`
  line
  line `(6) Where there is a dispute as to the person or persons entitled to compensation and the Tribunal`
  line `finds that more persons than one are entitled to compensation, it shall apportion the amount thereof`
  line `among such persons and in such manner as it thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(7) Nothing in the Arbitration Act, 1940 (10 of 1940), shall apply to any proceedings under this`
  line section.
  line
  line `^1[(8) The Tribunal, in the proceedings before it, shall have all the powers which a civil court has`
  line `while trying a suit under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following`
  line `matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(ii) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(iii) reception of evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(iv) requisitioning any public record from any court or office; and`
  line
  line `(v) issuing commissions for examination of witnesses.]`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (2119)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title Costs.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2119&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Every award made by the Tribunal shall also state the amount of costs incurred in the`
  line `proceedings before it and by what persons and in what proportions they are to be paid.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (2120)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Interest on awards.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2120&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `If the sum which in the opinion of the Tribunal ought to have been`
  line `awarded as compensation is in excess of the sum which the Central Government has stated to be a fair`
  line `amount of compensation, the award of the Tribunal may direct that the Central Government shall pay`
  line `interest on such excess at the rate of five per centum per annum from the date on which it became payable`
  line `to the date of payment of such excess.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (2121)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Payment of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 54 of 1971, s. 6, for "the second proviso" (w.e.f. 11-12-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2121&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any compensation payable under this Act may be tendered or`
  line `paid to the persons interested entitled thereto, and the Central Government shall pay it to them unless`
  line `prevented by some one or more of the contingencies mentioned in sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `(2) If the persons interested entitled thereto shall not consent to receive it or if there be any dispute as`
  line `to the sufficiency of the amount of compensation or the title to receive it or the apportionment thereof, the`
  line `Central Government shall deposit the amount of compensation with the Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided that any person admitted to be interested may receive such payment under protest as to the`
  line `sufficiency of the amount:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided further that every person who claims to be an interested person (whether such person has`
  line `been admitted to be interested or not) including the person referred to in the preceding proviso shall be`
  line `entitled to prefer a claim for compensation before the Tribunal:`
  line
  line `Provided also that no person who has received the amount otherwise than under protest shall be`
  line `entitled to prefer any such claim before the Tribunal.]`
  line
  line `(3) When the amount of compensation is not paid or deposited as required by this section, the Central`
  line `Government shall be liable to pay interest thereon at the rate of five per centum per annum from the time`
  line `the compensation became due until it shall have been so paid or deposited.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (2122)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Prospecting and mining to be done by Central Government in conformity with the Mineral Concession Rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2122&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Where prospecting is done under this Act by or on behalf of the Central`
  line `Government in any land situate within the jurisdiction of a State Government or where the Central`
  line `Government or a Government company has become the lessee of a State Government in respect of any`
  line `land under this Act, the terms and conditions under which the prospecting can be done or rights under the`
  line `lease exercised shall, as far as may be, be the same as the terms and conditions applicable to prospecting`
  line `licences and mining leases under the Mineral Concession Rules; and in case of doubt or dispute, shall be`
  line `settled by arbitration or in such other manner as the Central Government and the State Government may`
  line decide.
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18_a:
  sectionId (2123)
  sectionNo 18A
  orderNo 20
  title `Payment to State Governments in lieu of royalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 11-12-1971).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2123&sectionno=18A&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_18_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[18A. Payment to State Governments in lieu of royalty.--Notwithstanding anything contained in`
  line `this Act, where any land or any rights in or over land belonging to a State Government (other than the`
  line `rights under a mining lease granted or deemed to have been granted by the State Government to any`
  line `person) vest in the Central Government under section 10 or in a Government Company under section 11,`
  line `the Central Government or the Company, as the case may be, may pay to the State Government such sum`
  line `of money as would have been payable as royalty by a lessee had such land or rights been under a mining`
  line `lease granted by the State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (2124)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to delegate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2124&sectionno=19&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct`
  line `that all or any of the powers or duties which may be exercised or discharged by it under this Act shall, in`
  line `such circumstances and under such conditions, if any, as may be specified in the notification, be exercised`
  line `or discharged also by any person specified in this behalf in the notification and any such person may, with`
  line `the previous approval of the Central Government, by order in writing, direct that any power or duty which`
  line `has been directed to be exercised or discharged by him shall, in such circumstances and under such`
  line `conditions, if any, as may be specified in the direction, be exercised or discharged by any such person`
  line `subordinate to him as may be specified therein.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (2125)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 22
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2125&sectionno=20&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by any award of the Tribunal under section 14 may, within`
  line `thirty days from the date of such award, prefer an appeal to the High Court within whose jurisdiction the`
  line `land or some portion of the land which has been acquired or the land or some portion of the land covered`
  line `by a prospecting licence or by a mining lease in respect of which mining rights have been acquired is`
  line situate.
  line
  line `(2) Any person aggrieved by an order made by a competent authority or by any other person in virtue`
  line `of any powers exercisable by him under this Act may, within twenty-one days from the date of the order,`
  line `prefer an appeal to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(3) On receipt of an appeal under sub-section (2), the Central Government may, after calling for a`
  line `report from the competent authority of person concerned, and giving an opportunity to the parties to be`
  line `heard, and after making such further inquiry as may be necessary, pass such orders as it thinks fit, and the`
  line `order of the Central Government shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an appeal is preferred under sub-section (2), the Central Government may stay the`
  line `enforcement of the order of the competent authority or person concerned for such period and on such`
  line `conditions as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (2126)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to obtain information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2126&sectionno=21&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government or any person authorised in writing by`
  line `it in this behalf may, by order in writing, require any person to furnish to such authority as may be`
  line `specified in the order such information in his possession as may be required relating to any property in`
  line `respect of which action is proposed to be taken under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (2127)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 24
  title `Power to enter and inspect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2127&sectionno=22&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The competent authority, or any person authorised in writing by it`
  line `in this behalf, by general or special order, may enter and inspect any property for the purpose of`
  line `determining whether and, if so, in what manner an order under this Act should be made in relation to any`
  line `property or with a view to securing compliance with any order made under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (2128)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 25
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2128&sectionno=23&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `Whoever wilfully obstructs any person in doing any of the acts authorised by`
  line `sub-section (3) of section 4 or wilfully fills up, destroys, damages or displaces any mark made under`
  line `section 4, or wilfully obstructs the lawful exercise of any other power conferred by or under this Act, or`
  line `fails to comply with any order made or direction given under this Act, shall be punishable with`
  line `imprisonment which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or`
  line `with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (2129)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 26
  title `Service of notices and orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 58 of 1960, s. 3 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 26-12-1960).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2129&sectionno=24&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules that may be made under this Act, every`
  line `notice or order issued or made under this Act shall--`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a notice or order of a general nature or affecting a number of persons, be`
  line `notified in the Official Gazette and also published in the locality in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a notice or order directed to an individual ^1[be served on such individual],--`
  line
  line `(i) wherever it is practicable to do so by delivering or tendering it to that individual; or`
  line
  line `(ii) if it cannot be so delivered or tendered, by affixing it on the door or some other`
  line `conspicuous part of the residence in which that individual lives, and a written report thereof shall`
  line `be prepared and witnessed by two persons living in the neighbourhood; or`
  line
  line `(iii) failing service by these means, by post.`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (2130)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 27
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2130&sectionno=25&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Central Government or any person for anything which is in good faith done or`
  line `intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any rule or order made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Central Government or the competent`
  line `authority or any other person for any damage caused or likely to be caused by anything which is in good`
  line `faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (2131)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 28
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2131&sectionno=26&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided in this Act, no civil court`
  line `shall have jurisdiction in respect of any matter which the Central Government or the competent authority`
  line `or any other person is empowered by or under this Act to determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (2132)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 29
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 4 of 2005, s. 2 and the Schedule, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 11-1-2005).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2132&sectionno=27&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure to be followed in making any inquiry under this Act;`
  line
  line `(b) the procedure to be followed by the Tribunal in proceedings under section 14;`
  line
  line `(c) the form and manner in which appeals to the Central Government may be made under this`
  line `Act; and`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `^1[(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after`
  line `it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which`
  line `may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the`
  line `session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in`
  line `making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (2133)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 30
  title `Notifications under Act 1 of 1894 in which proceedings are pending to be treated as notifications under this Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514&sectionId=2133&sectionno=28&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_8_8_00006_195720_1517807322514
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every notification issued before the commencement of this Act,`
  line `whether by the Central Government or by a State Government, under section 4 of the Land Acquisition`
  line `Act, 1894 (1 of 1894) (hereinafter referred to as the said Act), in which lands were stated to be needed for`
  line `the prospecting of coal seams for the development of collieries to be worked by the Union of India shall`
  line `be deemed to have been issued by the Central Government under section 4 of this Act as if this Act had`
  line `been in force on the date of the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification issued before the commencement of this Act, whether by the Central`
  line `Government or by a State Government, under section 6 of the said Act in which lands were stated to be`
  line `needed for the development of coal shall be deemed to have been issued under section 9 of this Act as if`
  line `this Act had been in force on the date of the notification.`
  line
  line `(3) Any objection preferred under section 5A of the said Act in respect of any land covered by any`
  line `notification issued under section 4 of the said Act shall be deemed to be an objection preferred under`
  line `section 8 of this Act to the relevant competent authority and may be ^1[disposed of by him as if the`
  line `objection had been made in relation to a notification issued under section 7 of this Act ^2[in respect of such`
  line `land] or of any rights in or over such land; and the Central Government may at any time make a`
  line `declaration under section 9 of this Act in respect of the land or any part thereof or any rights in or over`
  line `such land or part].`
  line
  line `^3[(3A) Where in respect of any land covered by any notification issued under section 4 of the said Act,`
  line `no objection has been preferred under section 5A thereof within the period specified in that section, then`
  line `it shall be deemed that a notification had been issued under section 7 of this Act in respect of such land or`
  line `of any rights in or over such land and that no objection to the acquisition of the land or any rights in or`
  line `over the land had been preferred under section 8 of this Act, and accordingly the Central Government`
  line `may at any time make a declaration under section 9 of this Act in respect of the land or any part thereof or`
  line `any rights in or over such land or part.]`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the other provisions contained in this section, the provisions of this Act (including`
  line `provisions relating to compensation) shall apply in relation to any such notification as is referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) as they apply in relation to any notification issued under section 4 or`
  line `section 9, as the case may be, of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 51 of 1957, s. 7, for "disposed of by him accordingly" (w.e.f. 12-6-1957).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 23 of 1969, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 12-8-1969).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 23 of 1969, s. 2 (w.e.f. 12-8-1969).`
